# Enforce CRLF line endings in the working tree on every platform.
#
# `text=auto` lets git detect text files; `eol=crlf` forces those files to
# CRLF on checkout regardless of the contributor's `core.autocrlf` setting.
# Files are normalized to LF in the repository, so diffs/blame stay clean.
#
# After modifying this file, run `git add --renormalize .` to rewrite the
# index with the new attributes. Existing working-tree files keep their
# on-disk bytes; only the index is updated.

* text=auto eol=crlf

# Binary files — preserve bytes verbatim, no eol munging.
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.bmp   binary
*.ico   binary
*.tga   binary
*.blp   binary
*.pdf   binary
*.zip   binary
*.tar   binary
*.gz    binary
*.7z    binary
*.ttf   binary
*.otf   binary
